<li id="cite_note-Marie2016-103"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-Marie2016_103-0">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1215172403"><cite id="CITEREFMarie2016" class="citation web cs1">Marie, André (26 December 2016). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://catholicism.org/ad-rem-no-283.html">"Circumcision: An Acceptable Practice?"</a>. <a href="/wiki/The_Catholic_Thing" class="mw-redirect" title="The Catholic Thing">The Catholic Thing</a><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap">23 December</span> 2020</span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Circumcision%3A+An+Acceptable+Practice%3F&amp;rft.pub=The+Catholic+Thing&amp;rft.date=2016-12-26&amp;rft.aulast=Marie&amp;rft.aufirst=Andr%C3%A9&amp;rft_id=https%3A%2F%2Fcatholicism.org%2Fad-rem-no-283.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHygiene+in+Christianity" class="Z3988"></span></span>
